## C.1 [Easy — 100 points] — Distributed Protocols, Eventing & Modern AI
Integration

WebSub enables near-real-time distribution of updates on the Web. Name the
participants of a WebSub interaction and describe the sequence of
requests exchanged between them.

### Reference Solution

- **Participants:** subscriber, publisher, hub.
- **Interaction sequence:**
  1. Subscriber discovers the publisher's hub (e.g., via a `rel="hub"`
     link advertised by the publisher).
  2. Subscriber sends a subscription request (`POST`) to the hub.
  3. Hub verifies the subscription intent via a `GET` back to the
     subscriber.
  4. Publisher notifies the hub when new content is available.
  5. Hub fans out the update by `POST`-ing the content to the subscriber.
- Full credit requires naming all three participants and correctly
  describing the discovery + subscribe + verify + notify + fan-out
  sequence (dynamic hub discovery via links is a key detail).

